OL,3,CHealth board criticised after patient,
OL,4,C70, dies in 'unnecessary pain'
OL,6,FWales' Public Services Ombudsman,
OL,7,FMichelle Morris, told ITV Wales: "(Mrs
OL,8,FPicton's) final days and hours were,
OL,9,Fperhaps, not as comfortable as they
OL,10,Fshould have been.
OL,12,F"There was a concern her would have
OL,13,Fbeen in pain unnecessarily. It
OL,14,Fwouldn't have been dignified for her
OL,15,Fand that's what the family were
OL,16,Fconcerned about."
