OL,3,CHealth board criticised after patient,
OL,4,C70, dies in 'unnecessary pain'
OL,6,F"The Health Board has therefore not
OL,7,Fconfirmed if it accepts these
OL,8,Frecommendations and for that reason
OL,9,Fthis report has had to be issued as a
OL,10,Fpublic interest report.
OL,12,F"This is unacceptable and of serious
OL,13,Fconcern to the public."
OL,15,FIn her report, the Ombudsman made
OL,16,Frecommendations to the health board,
OL,17,Fincluding an apology to Mrs Williams
OL,18,Ffor the failings identified.
